1
00:00:19.194 --> 00:00:21.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, what do you think
of the O’Briens’ plan

2
00:00:21.753 --> 00:00:23.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to name their baby Sean?

3
00:00:24.991 --> 00:00:28.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I kind of like it.
Sean… has a nice ring to it.

4
00:00:28.231 --> 00:00:31.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except that in Bajoran
<i>Sean </i>means "swamp."

5
00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:33.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do the O’Briens know that?

6
00:00:33.429 --> 00:00:34.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I doubt it.

7
00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:36.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Someone should tell them.

8
00:00:36.428 --> 00:00:38.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I nominate you.

9
00:00:38.908 --> 00:00:40.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
DAX: Morning.

10
00:00:44.305 --> 00:00:45.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neck bothering you again?

11
00:00:45.906 --> 00:00:49.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s… it’s just a muscle pull.

12
00:00:49.264 --> 00:00:50.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is that?

13
00:00:50.704 --> 00:00:52.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The eighth muscle pull
this month?

14
00:00:52.383 --> 00:00:56.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, I believe
Commander Dax has been treated

15
00:00:56.623 --> 00:00:58.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for seven muscle pulls,

16
00:00:58.821 --> 00:01:00.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
two contusions, and
three cracked ribs.

17
00:01:01.208 --> 00:01:03.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The only person who’s spent
more time in the Infirmary

18
00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:06.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
over the past few weeks
is… Commander Worf.

19
00:01:06.819 --> 00:01:09.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn’t there any way the…
the two of you could, uh…

20
00:01:10.187 --> 00:01:11.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
uh, you know…

21
00:01:11.978 --> 00:01:13.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Make love?

22
00:01:13.217 --> 00:01:15.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Without injuring yourselves?

23
00:01:15.176 --> 00:01:17.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Interspecies romance
isn’t without its danger.

24
00:01:18.816 --> 00:01:20.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s part of the fun.

25
00:01:22.255 --> 00:01:24.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we’ll have
better luck on Risa.

26
00:01:24.333 --> 00:01:25.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Risa?

27
00:01:25.613 --> 00:01:27.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you and Worf

28
00:01:27.253 --> 00:01:28.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were taking your
vacation on Earth.

29
00:01:28.772 --> 00:01:31.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was his suggestion.

30
00:01:31.921 --> 00:01:32.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I changed his mind.

31
00:01:32.652 --> 00:01:34.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ODO: From what I hear

32
00:01:34.171 --> 00:01:38.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa make the Hoobishan Baths
look like a monastery.

33
00:01:38.169 --> 00:01:40.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope they have
a good hospital.

34
00:01:40.169 --> 00:01:41.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckling </i>)

35
00:01:42.568 --> 00:01:44.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
I can’t believe

36
00:01:44.248 --> 00:01:47.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you actually convinced Worf
to go to a pleasure planet.

37
00:01:47.127 --> 00:01:49.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He must really be loosening up.

38
00:01:49.527 --> 00:01:52.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hadn’t noticed it.

39
00:01:52.126 --> 00:01:53.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come to think of it,
neither have I.

40
00:01:53.885 --> 00:01:56.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, he’s still
the same old Worf.

41
00:01:56.284 --> 00:01:57.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Prune juice, extra large.

42
00:01:57.724 --> 00:01:59.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
See what I mean?

43
00:02:00.523 --> 00:02:01.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

44
00:02:05.722 --> 00:02:08.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain, Constable…

45
00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:10.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander.

46
00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:13.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, Dax said…
you were going to Risa.

47
00:02:13.639 --> 00:02:15.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did she?

48
00:02:16.558 --> 00:02:17.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, it’s no secret.

49
00:02:17.598 --> 00:02:19.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Apparently not.

50
00:02:19.717 --> 00:02:21.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must be
looking forward to it.

51
00:02:21.636 --> 00:02:23.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m looking forward
to spending some time alone

52
00:02:23.516 --> 00:02:25.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with Lieutenant Commander Dax.

53
00:02:25.195 --> 00:02:26.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn’t he sweet?

54
00:02:27.875 --> 00:02:29.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have much to discuss.

55
00:02:29.834 --> 00:02:30.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
About what?

56
00:02:30.953 --> 00:02:32.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a private matter.

57
00:02:32.793 --> 00:02:33.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

58
00:02:33.753 --> 00:02:35.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
Worf’s upset

59
00:02:35.112 --> 00:02:36.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I had lunch
with Captain Boday.

60
00:02:36.832 --> 00:02:37.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Gallamite?

61
00:02:38.323 --> 00:02:40.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His skull is transparent.

62
00:02:40.271 --> 00:02:41.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And if you couldn’t see
his brains,

63
00:02:41.471 --> 00:02:42.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
would it make you
feel any better?

64
00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:44.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is not proper
for you to have lunch

65
00:02:44.590 --> 00:02:46.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with an ex-lover
while we are together.

66
00:02:46.829 --> 00:02:49.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We were just talking.

67
00:02:49.228 --> 00:02:51.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to learn
to trust me a little more.

68
00:02:51.148 --> 00:02:52.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WORF:
I do trust you.

69
00:02:52.907 --> 00:02:56.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do not trust Captain Boday.

70
00:02:56.506 --> 00:02:58.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well…

71
00:02:58.505 --> 00:03:01.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can see it’s going to be
quite a trip.

72
00:03:02.664 --> 00:03:04.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, the two of you
have to tell us

73
00:03:04.584 --> 00:03:06.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
all about it
when you get back.

74
00:03:06.263 --> 00:03:08.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am sure <i>she </i>will.

75
00:03:12.221 --> 00:03:14.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not see why you
feel the need to talk

76
00:03:14.700 --> 00:03:16.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about our personal lives
to other people.

77
00:03:17.603 --> 00:03:18.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I don’t see why
you feel the need

78
00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:20.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to control my every move.

79
00:03:20.299 --> 00:03:21.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And they’re not other people.

80
00:03:21.779 --> 00:03:24.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Benjamin and Odo are my friends.

81
00:03:24.697 --> 00:03:26.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR:
Jadzia.

82
00:03:26.338 --> 00:03:27.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey.

83
00:03:27.297 --> 00:03:28.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

84
00:03:28.337 --> 00:03:29.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’ve been looking for you.

85
00:03:29.656 --> 00:03:30.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, I’ve been thinking
about this trip

86
00:03:30.896 --> 00:03:32.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’re taking
to Risa.

87
00:03:32.135 --> 00:03:33.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s a friend, too.

88
00:03:33.415 --> 00:03:34.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA: Julian and I
were talking it over,

89
00:03:34.895 --> 00:03:36.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and we’d like
to come along…

90
00:03:36.694 --> 00:03:37.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if that’s all right.

91
00:03:38.973 --> 00:03:40.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, we were hoping

92
00:03:40.892 --> 00:03:42.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to spend some time
alone together.

93
00:03:42.812 --> 00:03:44.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, you’ll have it.

94
00:03:44.292 --> 00:03:46.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, once we get to Risa,
you won’t even see us.

95
00:03:48.690 --> 00:03:51.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There’s no harm
in sharing a runabout.

96
00:03:53.972 --> 00:03:54.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose not.

97
00:03:54.289 --> 00:03:55.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh!
Thank you so much!

98
00:03:56.489 --> 00:03:57.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m going
to go pack.

99
00:03:57.808 --> 00:03:59.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander…

100
00:03:59.882 --> 00:04:00.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do not hug me.

101
00:04:00.567 --> 00:04:02.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I promise we’ll keep
out of your hair.

102
00:04:02.807 --> 00:04:04.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good.

103
00:04:04.446 --> 00:04:07.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because we have
much to discuss.

104
00:04:16.962 --> 00:04:19.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I really wish
I was going with you.

105
00:04:19.201 --> 00:04:22.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax and I had
some great times on Risa.

106
00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:24.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

107
00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:25.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Curzon Dax.

108
00:04:25.879 --> 00:04:27.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Curzon.

109
00:04:27.479 --> 00:04:28.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

110
00:04:31.877 --> 00:04:33.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have fun.

111
00:04:37.876 --> 00:04:40.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s about time you got here.

112
00:04:40.115 --> 00:04:42.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The rest of us were ready
to leave an hour ago.

113
00:04:42.914 --> 00:04:44.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is he doing here?

114
00:04:44.793 --> 00:04:46.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve always wanted
to go to Risa,

115
00:04:46.713 --> 00:04:47.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and this seemed like
a perfect opportunity.

116
00:04:48.728 --> 00:04:49.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He wouldn’t
give me any time off

117
00:04:49.393 --> 00:04:50.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
unless we promised
to take him with us.

118
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:52.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope this isn’t
going to be a problem.

119
00:04:52.311 --> 00:04:54.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK: Why should it
be a problem?

120
00:04:54.551 --> 00:04:56.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’re going to have
a wonderful time.

121
00:04:56.150 --> 00:04:58.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if you don’t mind,
Risa awaits.

122
00:05:00.149 --> 00:05:01.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

123
00:05:06.268 --> 00:05:07.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia…

124
00:05:09.586 --> 00:05:11.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know, I know.

125
00:05:11.146 --> 00:05:13.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have much to discuss.

126
00:07:16.748 --> 00:07:20.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let’s see… that’s
a Tarkalean tea for you,

127
00:07:20.627 --> 00:07:22.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a <i>raktajino </i>for you,

128
00:07:22.746 --> 00:07:24.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and an extra large
prune juice.

129
00:07:24.586 --> 00:07:26.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Leeta, you’re on vacation,
not at Quark’s.

130
00:07:26.585 --> 00:07:27.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You don’t have
to serve us.

131
00:07:27.825 --> 00:07:29.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, it gives me
something to do.

132
00:07:29.224 --> 00:07:30.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Space travel’s so dull.

133
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:33.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Have you ever noticed
how all stars look the same?

134
00:07:33.104 --> 00:07:35.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Excuse me…

135
00:07:35.502 --> 00:07:37.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
but I believe I ordered
a snail juice--

136
00:07:37.742 --> 00:07:38.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
hand-squeezed.

137
00:07:38.702 --> 00:07:39.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Get it yourself.

138
00:07:39.781 --> 00:07:40.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’m on vacation.

139
00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:42.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
How much longer
till we get there?

140
00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:44.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
DAX:
Another six hours.

141
00:07:44.740 --> 00:07:46.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
QUARK:
Six hours?

142
00:07:46.260 --> 00:07:48.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Tell the Ferengi
to return to his cabin.

143
00:07:48.419 --> 00:07:49.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You call that a cabin?

144
00:07:50.586 --> 00:07:52.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s a cot
and a waste disposal unit.

145
00:07:52.418 --> 00:07:54.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s so small
even I can’t stand up in there.

146
00:07:54.697 --> 00:07:56.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Look-- I’m developing a slouch.

147
00:07:56.816 --> 00:07:59.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Tell the Ferengi
to return to his cabin <i>now.</i>

148
00:07:59.256 --> 00:08:00.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Quark…

149
00:08:00.495 --> 00:08:01.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What’s he going to do?

150
00:08:01.654 --> 00:08:03.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Turn around
and take me home?

151
00:08:03.334 --> 00:08:04.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Ruin everyone’s vacation?

152
00:08:04.294 --> 00:08:05.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Coming about.

153
00:08:05.414 --> 00:08:06.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Setting course

154
00:08:06.694 --> 00:08:07.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for Deep Space 9.

155
00:08:07.653 --> 00:08:09.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Okay, okay.

156
00:08:09.453 --> 00:08:10.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You made your point.

157
00:08:10.971 --> 00:08:12.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’m going.

158
00:08:12.531 --> 00:08:16.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
But first, I have
a little present for everyone.

159
00:08:16.291 --> 00:08:17.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
One for you.

160
00:08:17.890 --> 00:08:20.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And one for you.

161
00:08:20.849 --> 00:08:23.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And one for you.

162
00:08:24.814 --> 00:08:26.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And none for you.

163
00:08:26.607 --> 00:08:27.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What’s this?

164
00:08:27.687 --> 00:08:28.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s a <i>Horga’hn.</i>

165
00:08:28.926 --> 00:08:32.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A Risian fertility symbol.

166
00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:33.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Displaying one
to the locals

167
00:08:33.645 --> 00:08:36.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
indicates you’re
seeking <i>jamaharon.</i>

168
00:08:36.644 --> 00:08:38.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
LEETA:
What’s <i>jamaharon?</i>

169
00:08:38.364 --> 00:08:41.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’ll show you later.

170
00:08:41.962 --> 00:08:43.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh.

171
00:08:43.562 --> 00:08:45.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Look.

172
00:08:45.561 --> 00:08:48.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They like each other.

173
00:08:48.161 --> 00:08:50.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I’m going
to be sick.

174
00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:52.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>All right. </i>I’m going.

175
00:08:52.439 --> 00:08:54.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

176
00:08:56.278 --> 00:08:57.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Going? Where?

177
00:08:58.784 --> 00:09:00.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m going to change
into something more comfortable.

178
00:09:00.797 --> 00:09:02.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don’t think
I’m going to beam down to Risa

179
00:09:02.516 --> 00:09:04.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dressed like this, do you?

180
00:09:06.763 --> 00:09:07.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s a good idea.

181
00:09:11.314 --> 00:09:12.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When in Rome…

182
00:09:14.833 --> 00:09:16.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

183
00:09:38.905 --> 00:09:40.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh!

184
00:09:40.585 --> 00:09:43.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t believe
we finally made it.

185
00:09:45.224 --> 00:09:47.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, enjoy your vacation.

186
00:09:47.863 --> 00:09:49.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm. We will.

187
00:09:49.263 --> 00:09:52.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Time to test
these babies out.

188
00:09:52.301 --> 00:09:54.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ladies…

189
00:09:56.820 --> 00:09:58.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seek <i>jamaharon?</i>

190
00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:01.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I seek whatever you’ve got.

191
00:10:01.459 --> 00:10:03.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All that is ours
is yours.

192
00:10:08.971 --> 00:10:09.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll take it.

193
00:10:12.775 --> 00:10:14.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Aren’t you uncomfortable
in that uniform?

194
00:10:14.975 --> 00:10:17.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Starfleet uniforms
are designed for comfort,

195
00:10:17.294 --> 00:10:20.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
even in the most
extreme environments.

196
00:10:20.940 --> 00:10:21.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you look
out of place.

197
00:10:22.134 --> 00:10:23.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I mean, look around you.

198
00:10:23.772 --> 00:10:25.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn’t it beautiful?

199
00:10:25.331 --> 00:10:27.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is an artificially
created paradise,

200
00:10:27.331 --> 00:10:29.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
maintained by the most elaborate
weather control system

201
00:10:29.811 --> 00:10:31.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Federation.

202
00:10:31.290 --> 00:10:33.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In its natural state,
Risa is nothing more

203
00:10:33.489 --> 00:10:35.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than a rain-soaked,
geologically unstable jungle.

204
00:10:35.888 --> 00:10:37.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe so,

205
00:10:37.368 --> 00:10:40.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the only dark cloud
I see around here is <i>you.</i>

206
00:10:40.247 --> 00:10:42.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not come here
to admire the scenery.

207
00:10:42.486 --> 00:10:44.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you say so.

208
00:10:44.366 --> 00:10:46.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess we should
just go home.

209
00:10:46.286 --> 00:10:47.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, maybe…

210
00:10:50.604 --> 00:10:52.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I would not be so hasty.

211
00:10:52.324 --> 00:10:54.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I take it
the scenery has improved.

212
00:10:56.362 --> 00:10:57.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A few months ago

213
00:10:57.842 --> 00:10:59.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when I was commanding
the <i>Defiant</i>

214
00:10:59.401 --> 00:11:01.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on a scouting mission
in the Gamma Quadrant,

215
00:11:01.201 --> 00:11:03.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we encountered
a protostar cluster--

216
00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:04.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a swirling mass of color

217
00:11:04.840 --> 00:11:06.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
set against
a background

218
00:11:07.796 --> 00:11:09.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of glowing clouds
and burning sky.

219
00:11:09.518 --> 00:11:13.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was the most beautiful thing
I’d ever seen…

220
00:11:13.317 --> 00:11:14.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until now.

221
00:11:17.356 --> 00:11:19.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve got to take you
on vacation more often.

222
00:11:22.435 --> 00:11:24.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dax, is that you?

223
00:11:25.553 --> 00:11:26.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Arandis.

224
00:11:26.793 --> 00:11:28.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was wondering
if you were still here.

225
00:11:28.712 --> 00:11:30.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh!

226
00:11:30.552 --> 00:11:32.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not only am I still here,
I have been promoted.

227
00:11:32.951 --> 00:11:35.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m Chief Facilitator for
the entire Temtibi Lagoon.

228
00:11:35.751 --> 00:11:38.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf, this is Arandis.

229
00:11:38.429 --> 00:11:39.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A friend
of Curzon’s.

230
00:11:39.750 --> 00:11:41.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She and Curzon spent
a lot of time together

231
00:11:41.509 --> 00:11:43.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on his last trip here.

232
00:11:43.428 --> 00:11:45.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had a wonderful time
together…

233
00:11:45.468 --> 00:11:46.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until I killed him.

234
00:11:46.867 --> 00:11:47.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Killed him?!

235
00:11:47.987 --> 00:11:50.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Death by <i>jamaharon.</i>

236
00:11:50.666 --> 00:11:52.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose there
are worse ways to go.

237
00:11:52.906 --> 00:11:55.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trust me, he died happy.

238
00:11:55.505 --> 00:11:57.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was such a sweet old man.

239
00:11:57.863 --> 00:11:59.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will take your word for it.

240
00:12:01.343 --> 00:12:02.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s so good
to see you again, Dax.

241
00:12:02.982 --> 00:12:05.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your new host
is very attractive.

242
00:12:05.262 --> 00:12:06.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

243
00:12:06.222 --> 00:12:07.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’d like to think so.

244
00:12:07.182 --> 00:12:08.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You haven’t aged
a day.

245
00:12:08.781 --> 00:12:10.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah… Risa’s been
very kind to me.

246
00:12:11.601 --> 00:12:12.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come, let me
show you around.

247
00:12:12.699 --> 00:12:13.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe later.

248
00:12:15.779 --> 00:12:16.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

249
00:12:17.188 --> 00:12:18.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All that is ours is yours.

250
00:12:18.897 --> 00:12:19.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

251
00:12:20.580 --> 00:12:21.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But we have everything we need.

252
00:12:29.550 --> 00:12:31.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That wasn’t very nice.

253
00:12:31.294 --> 00:12:33.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why? Is there something
of hers you want?

254
00:12:33.653 --> 00:12:36.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Arandis was Curzon’s lover,
not mine.

255
00:12:36.532 --> 00:12:38.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope you
remember that.

256
00:12:38.212 --> 00:12:40.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re still angry
about Captain Boday.

257
00:12:40.651 --> 00:12:42.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I <i>am </i>angry, it is because

258
00:12:42.730 --> 00:12:45.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you do not take our
relationship seriously.

259
00:12:45.489 --> 00:12:46.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf, we just got here.

260
00:12:46.650 --> 00:12:48.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do we have
to start arguing again?

261
00:12:48.569 --> 00:12:52.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you were a Klingon woman,
we would already be married.

262
00:12:52.128 --> 00:12:54.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In case you haven’t noticed,
I am not a Klingon woman.

263
00:12:54.527 --> 00:12:56.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is no excuse.

264
00:12:56.406 --> 00:12:59.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have been loyal to you,
and I expect you to be loyal

265
00:12:59.526 --> 00:13:00.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to me in return.

266
00:13:00.845 --> 00:13:02.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have been loyal to you,

267
00:13:02.444 --> 00:13:04.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m not going
to let you run my life.

268
00:13:04.364 --> 00:13:06.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m not trying to run your life.

269
00:13:06.203 --> 00:13:07.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then I’m going to go

270
00:13:07.563 --> 00:13:09.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and have a big glass
of icoberry juice.

271
00:13:09.642 --> 00:13:11.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is a mistake.

272
00:13:11.242 --> 00:13:13.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are allergic
to icoberry juice.

273
00:13:13.481 --> 00:13:15.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It makes your…

274
00:13:15.809 --> 00:13:16.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
spots itch.

275
00:13:16.521 --> 00:13:18.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I like the taste.

276
00:13:18.120 --> 00:13:21.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fine. Have as much
icoberry juice as you like,

277
00:13:21.638 --> 00:13:23.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but it is still a mistake.

278
00:13:23.238 --> 00:13:25.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it is my mistake
to make.

279
00:13:25.438 --> 00:13:27.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, why don’t you
go up to our room

280
00:13:27.877 --> 00:13:31.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and put on your bathing suit
so we can swim in the lagoon?

281
00:13:34.555 --> 00:13:35.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you wish.

282
00:13:38.834 --> 00:13:40.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

283
00:13:40.753 --> 00:13:42.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enter.

284
00:13:46.191 --> 00:13:47.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope I’m not disturbing you,

285
00:13:47.631 --> 00:13:48.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Commander.

286
00:13:48.911 --> 00:13:49.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My name is

287
00:13:49.871 --> 00:13:51.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pascal Fullerton.

288
00:13:51.470 --> 00:13:53.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m the chairman of the
New Essentialists Movement.

289
00:13:53.349 --> 00:13:55.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m not familiar
with that organization.

290
00:13:55.469 --> 00:13:57.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’re dedicated to restoring

291
00:13:57.188 --> 00:13:59.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the moral and cultural
traditions of the Federation.

292
00:14:00.273 --> 00:14:02.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is a statement
of our principles.

293
00:14:02.707 --> 00:14:04.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But if you would
like to hear more,

294
00:14:04.226 --> 00:14:06.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we’re holding a rally
later this afternoon.

295
00:14:06.385 --> 00:14:07.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On Risa?

296
00:14:07.465 --> 00:14:09.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What better place?

297
00:14:09.104 --> 00:14:11.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This world revels in the kind
of self-indulgence

298
00:14:11.504 --> 00:14:14.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that’s eroding the foundations
of Federation society.

299
00:14:14.982 --> 00:14:16.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We intend to shut it down.

300
00:14:28.418 --> 00:14:30.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I really wish you’d
stop reading that.

301
00:14:30.898 --> 00:14:33.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would not dismiss
Fullerton so quickly.

302
00:14:33.537 --> 00:14:35.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His analysis
of recent Federation history

303
00:14:35.737 --> 00:14:37.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is both insightful
and disturbing.

304
00:14:37.256 --> 00:14:38.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What’s really
disturbing

305
00:14:38.776 --> 00:14:40.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is that you’re still
wearing your uniform.

306
00:14:40.335 --> 00:14:43.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It would not hurt you
to read this.

307
00:14:45.413 --> 00:14:46.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
Mmm…

308
00:14:47.933 --> 00:14:49.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
mmm!

309
00:14:49.452 --> 00:14:52.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, the truth is

310
00:14:52.924 --> 00:14:54.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
not everyone can
be a dabo girl.

311
00:14:54.131 --> 00:14:55.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First of all,

312
00:14:55.970 --> 00:14:57.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you have to be able
to wear the clothes,

313
00:14:57.890 --> 00:15:00.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and believe me,
that’s not easy.

314
00:15:00.409 --> 00:15:01.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to be able

315
00:15:02.882 --> 00:15:04.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to calculate odds in
your head very quickly,

316
00:15:04.768 --> 00:15:06.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and most importantly,

317
00:15:06.328 --> 00:15:08.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you need a very
supple wrist…

318
00:15:08.726 --> 00:15:10.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
like this.

319
00:15:12.165 --> 00:15:13.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

320
00:15:13.965 --> 00:15:15.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX: …the end of
the Federation

321
00:15:15.525 --> 00:15:17.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
since the day
it was founded.

322
00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:18.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trust me. I know.

323
00:15:18.323 --> 00:15:19.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, hi!

324
00:15:19.443 --> 00:15:21.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leeta, what a surprise.

325
00:15:21.163 --> 00:15:22.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Care to join us?

326
00:15:22.403 --> 00:15:24.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were just about
to take a reyamilk soak.

327
00:15:24.122 --> 00:15:26.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe later.

328
00:15:26.761 --> 00:15:28.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

329
00:15:28.801 --> 00:15:30.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Worf.</i>

330
00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:35.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sigh of contentment </i>)

331
00:15:35.399 --> 00:15:38.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was not Dr. Bashir.

332
00:15:38.278 --> 00:15:40.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s none of our business.

333
00:15:40.637 --> 00:15:42.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you defending
her actions?

334
00:15:42.636 --> 00:15:43.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am not
defending anything,

335
00:15:44.367 --> 00:15:45.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it’s not my
business or yours.

336
00:15:45.956 --> 00:15:47.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, what do you
say we go sign out

337
00:15:47.955 --> 00:15:50.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a couple of floaters
and take in the sights?

338
00:15:50.314 --> 00:15:51.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I cannot.

339
00:15:51.474 --> 00:15:52.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Essentialists
are having a rally,

340
00:15:53.739 --> 00:15:54.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I plan to attend.

341
00:15:54.513 --> 00:15:55.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( <i>sighs </i>):
You’re kidding.

342
00:15:58.326 --> 00:15:59.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re not kidding.

343
00:16:08.829 --> 00:16:11.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t these people have
anything better to do?

344
00:16:12.285 --> 00:16:13.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps you
underestimate

345
00:16:13.707 --> 00:16:16.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the power of
Fullerton’s message.

346
00:16:16.147 --> 00:16:17.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The plot thickens.

347
00:16:19.505 --> 00:16:20.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you were worried

348
00:16:20.945 --> 00:16:22.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
about Julian.

349
00:16:24.144 --> 00:16:27.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why are he and Leeta
not together?

350
00:16:27.183 --> 00:16:29.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t know, but don’t
jump to conclusions.

351
00:16:29.983 --> 00:16:32.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m sure there’s
a reasonable explanation.

352
00:16:32.501 --> 00:16:35.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This place is
a bad influence on people.

353
00:16:35.301 --> 00:16:36.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARANDIS:
Here for the show?

354
00:16:36.981 --> 00:16:39.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would not call it
a show.

355
00:16:39.379 --> 00:16:42.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? I find Mr. Fullerton
very entertaining.

356
00:16:42.339 --> 00:16:44.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He seems
pretty determined

357
00:16:44.178 --> 00:16:46.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to discourage people
from coming here.

358
00:16:46.657 --> 00:16:48.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa receives millions
of visitors every year.

359
00:16:48.777 --> 00:16:50.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And all of them leave happier
than when they’ve arrived.

360
00:16:50.696 --> 00:16:51.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t see how one man,

361
00:16:52.564 --> 00:16:53.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
no matter how determined,
can change that.

362
00:16:53.895 --> 00:16:56.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kahless fought off an entire
army at Three Turn Bridge,

363
00:16:56.614 --> 00:16:58.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and <i>he </i>was only one man.

364
00:16:58.294 --> 00:16:59.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fullerton and his
Essentialists

365
00:16:59.574 --> 00:17:00.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have been here
for about a month,

366
00:17:00.973 --> 00:17:02.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and no matter
how many speeches he gives,

367
00:17:02.733 --> 00:17:06.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the water’s still warm,
and the wind still smells sweet.

368
00:17:06.651 --> 00:17:09.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, if he’s enjoying himself,
who are we to discourage him?

369
00:17:11.770 --> 00:17:13.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>scattered applause </i>)

370
00:17:18.482 --> 00:17:19.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s right.

371
00:17:19.687 --> 00:17:21.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take a good look.

372
00:17:21.487 --> 00:17:24.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can only imagine
what you must think of me--

373
00:17:24.606 --> 00:17:27.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a middle-aged,
ponderous academic,

374
00:17:27.855 --> 00:17:28.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
sweating under
the hot Risian suns,

375
00:17:28.685 --> 00:17:31.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
wasting his time
telling you things

376
00:17:31.204 --> 00:17:33.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you don’t want
to hear.

377
00:17:33.523 --> 00:17:36.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you know what I see
when I look at you?

378
00:17:36.883 --> 00:17:38.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Children…

379
00:17:38.522 --> 00:17:41.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
pampered, spoiled children.

380
00:17:41.761 --> 00:17:44.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For some reason, the
citizens of the Federation

381
00:17:44.680 --> 00:17:45.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
have come to believe

382
00:17:46.803 --> 00:17:47.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that they are entitled
to lives of ease….

383
00:17:47.759 --> 00:17:48.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I may be wrong,

384
00:17:48.998 --> 00:17:50.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but didn’t he
just insult us?

385
00:17:50.158 --> 00:17:51.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you want
something to eat,

386
00:17:51.438 --> 00:17:53.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you get it from
a replicator.

387
00:17:53.237 --> 00:17:56.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you want amusement,
you go to a holosuite,

388
00:17:56.917 --> 00:18:01.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and if you need protection,
you call for Starfleet.

389
00:18:01.115 --> 00:18:03.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But someday…

390
00:18:03.114 --> 00:18:04.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
someday soon,

391
00:18:04.874 --> 00:18:06.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’re going to
have to learn

392
00:18:06.634 --> 00:18:08.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to take care
of yourselves,

393
00:18:08.193 --> 00:18:10.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because if <i>I </i>see you
as helpless children,

394
00:18:10.832 --> 00:18:13.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then how do you think
the Borg see you?

395
00:18:13.232 --> 00:18:16.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or the Romulans or the Klingons
or the Dominion?

396
00:18:16.910 --> 00:18:19.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These empires look
at the Federation,

397
00:18:19.309 --> 00:18:21.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they see a prize--

398
00:18:21.389 --> 00:18:24.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a prize that we have
forgotten how to protect,

399
00:18:24.188 --> 00:18:26.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and if we don’t change our ways,

400
00:18:26.587 --> 00:18:28.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they’re going to take it
from us.

401
00:18:28.827 --> 00:18:32.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Fullerton has quite
a flair for the dramatic.

402
00:18:32.185 --> 00:18:34.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Does he <i>really </i>believe that?

403
00:18:34.505 --> 00:18:35.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think he does.

404
00:18:35.624 --> 00:18:37.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
…and re-embrace

405
00:18:37.105 --> 00:18:38.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the kind of hard work

406
00:18:38.944 --> 00:18:41.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that built the Federation
in the first place.

407
00:18:41.823 --> 00:18:44.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or we can lie here,
napping in the sun,

408
00:18:44.182 --> 00:18:46.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until we wake up

409
00:18:46.221 --> 00:18:50.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with Jem’Hadar guns
to our heads.

410
00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:53.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The choice is ours.

411
00:18:53.859 --> 00:18:56.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Heaven help us
if we make the wrong one.

412
00:19:00.177 --> 00:19:02.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR: What <i>are </i>you
talking about?

413
00:19:02.336 --> 00:19:04.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Worf, this sounds
like nonsense.

414
00:19:04.296 --> 00:19:05.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am merely observing

415
00:19:05.736 --> 00:19:07.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that the Klingons would
never have attacked

416
00:19:07.295 --> 00:19:09.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
had they not believed
the Federation vulnerable.

417
00:19:09.614 --> 00:19:11.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even now, since
the changeling

418
00:19:11.174 --> 00:19:12.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
was discovered on the
Klingon High Council,

419
00:19:12.854 --> 00:19:15.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
most of my people
continue to call for war,

420
00:19:15.133 --> 00:19:17.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because they think
they can win.

421
00:19:17.372 --> 00:19:19.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of this has
anything to do with Risa.

422
00:19:19.732 --> 00:19:20.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cannot be certain of that.

423
00:19:20.891 --> 00:19:22.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
All I know is

424
00:19:22.451 --> 00:19:24.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve spent lifetimes
defending the Federation,

425
00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:27.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I deserve a vacation
every now and then.

426
00:19:28.649 --> 00:19:29.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Julian?

427
00:19:30.768 --> 00:19:32.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, <i>there </i>you are.

428
00:19:32.647 --> 00:19:34.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am so glad we came here.

429
00:19:34.327 --> 00:19:36.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m having
the most wonderful time.

430
00:19:36.766 --> 00:19:38.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you this was
just what we needed.

431
00:19:38.486 --> 00:19:39.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm…

432
00:19:41.765 --> 00:19:43.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Something wrong?

433
00:19:43.204 --> 00:19:44.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s nothing.

434
00:19:44.884 --> 00:19:47.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You two dishonor each other
with your actions.

435
00:19:48.433 --> 00:19:50.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
what he’s talking about?

436
00:19:50.362 --> 00:19:54.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean… we didn’t tell you
why we came here?

437
00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:58.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’re conducting
the Rite of Separation.

438
00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:00.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s an old Bajoran custom.

439
00:20:00.399 --> 00:20:02.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When a couple separates,

440
00:20:02.118 --> 00:20:04.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they spend several days
celebrating their parting.

441
00:20:04.478 --> 00:20:07.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s a way to remember
all the good times

442
00:20:07.438 --> 00:20:10.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and to seek out
new opportunities.

443
00:20:10.597 --> 00:20:13.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A very wise and ancient culture.

444
00:20:13.635 --> 00:20:15.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
You know, Julian,

445
00:20:15.355 --> 00:20:17.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t think

446
00:20:17.114 --> 00:20:19.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve completely gotten you
out of my system yet.

447
00:20:19.754 --> 00:20:21.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know exactly
what you mean.

448
00:20:21.953 --> 00:20:23.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse us.

449
00:20:23.753 --> 00:20:27.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, we have a few…
details to work out.

450
00:20:33.910 --> 00:20:35.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Terminating
a relationship

451
00:20:35.629 --> 00:20:37.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
should not be taken
so frivolously.

452
00:20:37.588 --> 00:20:39.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not every relationship

453
00:20:39.267 --> 00:20:41.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
has to end like
a Klingon opera.

454
00:20:41.187 --> 00:20:42.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no, no.

455
00:20:42.827 --> 00:20:44.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just the ones that
are important.

456
00:20:44.546 --> 00:20:46.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>furniture breaking </i>)

457
00:20:49.385 --> 00:20:50.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stay where you are.

458
00:21:03.740 --> 00:21:05.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On three.

459
00:21:05.100 --> 00:21:06.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One, two…

460
00:21:06.699 --> 00:21:07.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait.

461
00:21:07.739 --> 00:21:09.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s enough.

462
00:21:10.779 --> 00:21:14.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well… I hope
we’ve proved our point.

463
00:21:16.616 --> 00:21:18.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The power cells
are empty.

464
00:21:18.615 --> 00:21:20.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have no intention
of harming anyone.

465
00:21:20.855 --> 00:21:23.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t understand.

466
00:21:23.951 --> 00:21:26.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think you’re safe here
in this "paradise" of yours,

467
00:21:26.293 --> 00:21:27.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you’re not.

468
00:21:27.773 --> 00:21:29.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What if we had been Jem’Hadar

469
00:21:29.492 --> 00:21:31.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or Klingons
or Romulans.

470
00:21:31.652 --> 00:21:32.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm?

471
00:21:32.972 --> 00:21:34.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’d be dead now.

472
00:21:34.930 --> 00:21:37.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Even you-- Starfleet officers--

473
00:21:37.371 --> 00:21:40.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were lulled into a false
sense of security.

474
00:21:40.209 --> 00:21:42.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you could be taken unaware,

475
00:21:42.529 --> 00:21:45.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what chance
do the rest of us have?

476
00:21:45.408 --> 00:21:47.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The sad truth is

477
00:21:47.887 --> 00:21:50.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the galaxy is a hostile place.

478
00:21:50.766 --> 00:21:55.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Forget that, even for a moment,
and you risk losing <i>everything.</i>

479
00:21:55.445 --> 00:21:57.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just something
for you

480
00:21:57.245 --> 00:22:00.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to think about while you wait
for your desserts.

481
00:22:01.643 --> 00:22:03.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

482
00:22:03.123 --> 00:22:04.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on, demonstration’s over.

483
00:22:04.828 --> 00:22:05.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Move along, move along.

484
00:22:05.322 --> 00:22:07.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a Starfleet officer,
I have the authority

485
00:22:07.682 --> 00:22:09.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to arrest you
for what you just did.

486
00:22:09.841 --> 00:22:11.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But that would be
a waste of time.

487
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:13.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We both know the Risians
won’t prosecute.

488
00:22:13.479 --> 00:22:15.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They don’t have
the courage for it.

489
00:22:15.958 --> 00:22:17.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Believe me, I wish they did.

490
00:22:17.958 --> 00:22:19.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander Worf…

491
00:22:19.318 --> 00:22:22.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what did you think of
our little demonstration?

492
00:22:22.597 --> 00:22:25.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I cannot condone
what you have done.

493
00:22:25.476 --> 00:22:26.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe not…

494
00:22:26.795 --> 00:22:28.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I do think
you understand it.

495
00:22:43.230 --> 00:22:45.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

496
00:22:49.589 --> 00:22:52.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t know about you,
but it’s past my bedtime.

497
00:22:54.281 --> 00:22:55.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need to talk.

498
00:22:55.627 --> 00:22:57.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
About the Essentialists?

499
00:22:58.261 --> 00:23:00.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. About us.

500
00:23:00.225 --> 00:23:04.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I suppose you have another
list of things I’m doing wrong.

501
00:23:04.224 --> 00:23:06.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not say you were
doing anything wrong.

502
00:23:07.633 --> 00:23:08.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s just that…

503
00:23:08.383 --> 00:23:10.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
some of your behavior…

504
00:23:10.582 --> 00:23:12.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about my behavior?

505
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:14.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At times, you are too impulsive.

506
00:23:14.581 --> 00:23:16.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You-you act without thinking.

507
00:23:16.501 --> 00:23:18.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have no
self-control.

508
00:23:18.260 --> 00:23:20.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you think
I need you to control me?

509
00:23:21.499 --> 00:23:24.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia, you are my <i>par’machkai,</i>

510
00:23:24.898 --> 00:23:27.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that means everything
you do reflects on me.

511
00:23:27.857 --> 00:23:29.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry if I embarrass you.

512
00:23:29.816 --> 00:23:33.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just need to know
that you take this relationship

513
00:23:33.655 --> 00:23:35.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as seriously
as I do.

514
00:23:35.454 --> 00:23:37.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I just wish
you’d relax a little

515
00:23:37.854 --> 00:23:40.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and let yourself enjoy
what we have together.

516
00:23:44.492 --> 00:23:48.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, I’m not going
to change who I am.

517
00:23:48.811 --> 00:23:50.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nor am I.

518
00:23:50.970 --> 00:23:53.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, at least we agree
on something.

519
00:23:56.369 --> 00:23:57.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

520
00:23:59.688 --> 00:24:01.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t we go to bed?

521
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:03.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You go.

522
00:24:03.367 --> 00:24:05.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will be there shortly.

523
00:24:07.165 --> 00:24:08.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

524
00:24:11.124 --> 00:24:13.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

525
00:24:19.962 --> 00:24:21.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This place looks
a lot better

526
00:24:21.761 --> 00:24:23.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than it did
last night.

527
00:24:23.360 --> 00:24:25.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess the Risians
aren’t as lethargic

528
00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:27.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as the Essentialists would
like everyone to believe.

529
00:24:28.397 --> 00:24:30.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Essentialists are
wrong about many things.

530
00:24:30.718 --> 00:24:34.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What Mr. Fullerton could use
is a little <i>jamaharon.</i>

531
00:24:34.877 --> 00:24:36.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No…

532
00:24:36.196 --> 00:24:37.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a lot of <i>jamaharon.</i>

533
00:24:39.956 --> 00:24:43.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d buy him a <i>Horga’hn </i>myself
if I thought he’d take it.

534
00:24:43.435 --> 00:24:46.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

535
00:24:46.233 --> 00:24:47.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It looks like
he’s not the only one

536
00:24:47.793 --> 00:24:49.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that could use some cheering up.

537
00:24:49.273 --> 00:24:51.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ve had better vacations.

538
00:24:51.712 --> 00:24:53.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better than Risa?

539
00:24:53.152 --> 00:24:55.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

540
00:24:55.471 --> 00:24:57.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ve never known a Klingon

541
00:24:57.310 --> 00:24:59.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who had a tougher time
enjoying himself.

542
00:25:00.697 --> 00:25:02.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s no reason for you
not to have a good time.

543
00:25:02.629 --> 00:25:05.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa is famous
for its diversions.

544
00:25:05.628 --> 00:25:08.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish it were that simple.

545
00:25:08.666 --> 00:25:10.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was for Curzon Dax.

546
00:25:10.466 --> 00:25:11.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

547
00:25:11.426 --> 00:25:12.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I can tell

548
00:25:12.866 --> 00:25:15.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there’s more
than a little Curzon in you.

549
00:25:15.225 --> 00:25:17.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He loved this planet.

550
00:25:18.645 --> 00:25:19.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And Risa loved him.

551
00:25:21.743 --> 00:25:23.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t I help you clean up?

552
00:25:26.101 --> 00:25:28.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All that is ours is yours.

553
00:25:30.220 --> 00:25:32.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
Our paths have grown apart.

554
00:25:39.537 --> 00:25:42.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was one is now two.

555
00:25:44.376 --> 00:25:47.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The time for sharing
is over.

556
00:25:53.543 --> 00:25:54.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
May the Prophets guide you

557
00:25:54.893 --> 00:25:56.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
toward the path of happiness.

558
00:25:56.852 --> 00:25:59.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And may they walk
with you always.

559
00:26:12.447 --> 00:26:13.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s it?

560
00:26:13.727 --> 00:26:15.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s it.

561
00:26:15.207 --> 00:26:16.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What were
you expecting?

562
00:26:16.607 --> 00:26:18.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was expecting
fireworks.

563
00:26:18.566 --> 00:26:19.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where’s the anger?

564
00:26:19.965 --> 00:26:21.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The vicious
name-calling?

565
00:26:21.805 --> 00:26:23.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The irrational
accusations?

566
00:26:23.444 --> 00:26:25.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never would have agreed
to be a witness

567
00:26:25.484 --> 00:26:28.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I’d known you were going
to be so <i>civil.</i>

568
00:26:28.283 --> 00:26:29.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s disgusting.

569
00:26:29.803 --> 00:26:31.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Personally, I think
it was admirable--

570
00:26:31.642 --> 00:26:33.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
no recriminations,
no hurt feelings.

571
00:26:33.681 --> 00:26:35.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t think I’ve
ever felt this good

572
00:26:35.921 --> 00:26:37.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the end
of a relationship.

573
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:38.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I agree.

574
00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:41.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now I can finally be honest
about my feelings.

575
00:26:41.200 --> 00:26:43.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What… does
that mean?

576
00:26:43.478 --> 00:26:46.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s just…

577
00:26:46.198 --> 00:26:48.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the past
few months,

578
00:26:48.597 --> 00:26:52.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve been… thinking a lot
about another man.

579
00:26:52.956 --> 00:26:54.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ahh…

580
00:26:54.356 --> 00:26:55.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let me get
this straight.

581
00:26:55.875 --> 00:26:57.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
While you were still
dating Julian here,

582
00:26:57.914 --> 00:27:00.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you were having fantasies
about someone else?

583
00:27:00.354 --> 00:27:02.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’d rather not discuss it now.

584
00:27:02.233 --> 00:27:03.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, no, no, no.
You brought it up.

585
00:27:03.632 --> 00:27:05.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You might as well
tell me who it is.

586
00:27:05.512 --> 00:27:06.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, do tell.

587
00:27:06.871 --> 00:27:08.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

588
00:27:08.151 --> 00:27:09.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s…

589
00:27:11.950 --> 00:27:13.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

590
00:27:13.869 --> 00:27:15.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your brother…

591
00:27:15.669 --> 00:27:17.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rom.

592
00:27:17.109 --> 00:27:19.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My brother Rom?

593
00:27:19.148 --> 00:27:20.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His brother Rom?

594
00:27:20.668 --> 00:27:22.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s so cute…

595
00:27:22.707 --> 00:27:24.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and very sexy.

596
00:27:24.746 --> 00:27:26.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Cute"?

597
00:27:26.706 --> 00:27:28.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Sexy"?

598
00:27:28.305 --> 00:27:29.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Rom?
-Rom?

599
00:27:31.144 --> 00:27:32.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here.

600
00:27:32.424 --> 00:27:34.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You need this
more than I do.

601
00:27:48.419 --> 00:27:51.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARANDIS: Just close your eyes
and watch your body.

602
00:27:51.259 --> 00:27:54.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let all the tension drain away.

603
00:27:54.979 --> 00:27:56.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doesn’t the clay feel good?

604
00:27:56.337 --> 00:27:58.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wonderful.

605
00:27:58.968 --> 00:28:01.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now pour your emotions
into it.

606
00:28:01.215 --> 00:28:02.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin to mold it.

607
00:28:02.814 --> 00:28:04.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Feel the texture
in your hands.

608
00:28:04.894 --> 00:28:06.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do.

609
00:28:06.214 --> 00:28:08.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I feel it.
I really do.

610
00:28:08.653 --> 00:28:11.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew you’d get it.

611
00:28:11.133 --> 00:28:12.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dax.

612
00:28:12.971 --> 00:28:14.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf!

613
00:28:18.290 --> 00:28:20.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf?

614
00:28:44.722 --> 00:28:46.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m tired of giving speeches.

615
00:28:46.721 --> 00:28:48.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s time we took action.

616
00:28:48.361 --> 00:28:50.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’ve taken action--
the raid on the solarium.

617
00:28:50.761 --> 00:28:52.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’ll be forgotten
by tomorrow.

618
00:28:52.240 --> 00:28:53.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door opens </i>)

619
00:28:55.279 --> 00:28:56.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf?

620
00:29:00.957 --> 00:29:03.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You want to make
people leave Risa…

621
00:29:03.597 --> 00:29:05.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I know a way.

622
00:29:13.914 --> 00:29:16.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I probably would have reacted
the same way Worf did.

623
00:29:16.152 --> 00:29:18.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, I know Arandis is
Curzon’s lover, not yours

624
00:29:19.722 --> 00:29:21.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if I’d walked in on the two
of you together, well…

625
00:29:21.631 --> 00:29:23.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
trying to figure you out
at any given time isn’t easy.

626
00:29:23.990 --> 00:29:25.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I like that
about her.

627
00:29:25.270 --> 00:29:26.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So do I.

628
00:29:26.869 --> 00:29:28.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s the reason why I
chased after her so long.

629
00:29:28.429 --> 00:29:30.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Would you two please

630
00:29:30.308 --> 00:29:32.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
stop talking about me
like I’m not here?

631
00:29:32.588 --> 00:29:34.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s also the reason why I
stopped chasing after her.

632
00:29:34.987 --> 00:29:36.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re too much work.

633
00:29:36.427 --> 00:29:38.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Worf </i>is the one
who’s too much work.

634
00:29:38.586 --> 00:29:41.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What you need is a Ferengi.

635
00:29:41.385 --> 00:29:42.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe,

636
00:29:42.665 --> 00:29:45.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but what I want is Worf.

637
00:29:45.544 --> 00:29:46.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

638
00:29:47.237 --> 00:29:51.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because he has the courage
of a berserker cat,

639
00:29:51.182 --> 00:29:53.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and he has the heart of a poet.

640
00:29:53.822 --> 00:29:55.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the brain
of a pigheaded idiot.

641
00:29:55.900 --> 00:29:57.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, sometimes.

642
00:29:59.599 --> 00:30:00.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia.

643
00:30:00.699 --> 00:30:01.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

644
00:30:01.659 --> 00:30:02.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m afraid not.

645
00:30:02.939 --> 00:30:04.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of the staff
can find him,

646
00:30:04.379 --> 00:30:05.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m sure
he’ll turn up.

647
00:30:05.818 --> 00:30:08.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, no sense
waiting around here for him.

648
00:30:08.777 --> 00:30:10.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I say we take some floaters
up into the hills

649
00:30:10.697 --> 00:30:13.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and go skinny-dipping
in the hot springs.

650
00:30:13.175 --> 00:30:14.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never thought
I’d say this,

651
00:30:14.455 --> 00:30:15.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I’m with Quark.

652
00:30:15.535 --> 00:30:17.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that?

653
00:30:17.535 --> 00:30:19.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Great. Just
what we needed.

654
00:30:19.893 --> 00:30:21.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought it wasn’t
supposed to rain

655
00:30:21.213 --> 00:30:22.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in this part of Risa.

656
00:30:22.173 --> 00:30:23.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s not.

657
00:30:23.932 --> 00:30:26.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Something must be wrong
with the weather grid.

658
00:30:26.920 --> 00:30:27.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>thunder rumbles </i>)

659
00:30:36.368 --> 00:30:38.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I have your
attention, please.

660
00:30:38.448 --> 00:30:40.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously, the weather grid
is experiencing

661
00:30:40.647 --> 00:30:42.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
some type of malfunction,

662
00:30:42.447 --> 00:30:45.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m sure we’ll be able
to repair it soon.

663
00:30:45.126 --> 00:30:46.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No…

664
00:30:46.286 --> 00:30:47.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you won’t.

665
00:30:47.846 --> 00:30:49.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re responsible
for this.

666
00:30:49.524 --> 00:30:51.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I authorized it,
but it was not my idea.

667
00:30:52.423 --> 00:30:53.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was mine.

668
00:30:53.724 --> 00:30:55.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you serious?

669
00:30:55.443 --> 00:30:57.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s serious.

670
00:30:57.482 --> 00:30:59.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, what did you do,
build an uplink

671
00:30:59.521 --> 00:31:01.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so you could take control
of the weather grid?

672
00:31:01.842 --> 00:31:03.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The grid has been deactivated.

673
00:31:03.441 --> 00:31:05.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It will take three or four days
to restore the system

674
00:31:05.840 --> 00:31:07.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to normal operation.

675
00:31:07.280 --> 00:31:08.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
During that time,
the inhabitants of Risa

676
00:31:08.919 --> 00:31:10.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and their guests will experience

677
00:31:10.798 --> 00:31:12.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the planet’s
natural weather cycle.

678
00:31:12.837 --> 00:31:13.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And for most on Risa,

679
00:31:14.776 --> 00:31:15.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that means rain,
and plenty of it.

680
00:31:15.877 --> 00:31:18.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But why are you doing this?

681
00:31:18.196 --> 00:31:19.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because Risa is an illusion

682
00:31:19.636 --> 00:31:21.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
created
by weather control systems,

683
00:31:21.995 --> 00:31:24.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
industrial replicators,
seismic regulators.

684
00:31:24.595 --> 00:31:27.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the Federation
is going to survive,

685
00:31:27.314 --> 00:31:29.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we’re going to have to stop
wasting our time with toys

686
00:31:30.734 --> 00:31:32.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and get back to the essentials.

687
00:31:34.631 --> 00:31:36.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m beginning to think
there’s no hope for that man.

688
00:31:37.311 --> 00:31:38.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>thunder crashes </i>)

689
00:31:38.510 --> 00:31:41.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or for you, either, Mr. Worf.

690
00:31:45.908 --> 00:31:47.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander,
with all due respect,

691
00:31:47.867 --> 00:31:49.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
are you out of your mind?

692
00:31:49.907 --> 00:31:52.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I think you will find me
quite rational.

693
00:31:52.306 --> 00:31:54.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As rational
as Klingons get, anyway.

694
00:31:54.105 --> 00:31:55.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, this
is wrong.

695
00:31:55.265 --> 00:31:56.945 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I disagree.

696
00:31:57.249 --> 00:32:00.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If Federation citizens cannot
handle a little bad weather,

697
00:32:00.303 --> 00:32:02.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how will they handle
a Dominion invasion?

698
00:32:12.459 --> 00:32:14.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( <i>thunder crashing,</i>
<i>wind whistling </i>)

699
00:32:17.619 --> 00:32:20.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have seen drier days
on Ferenginar

700
00:32:20.737 --> 00:32:24.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and we have 178
different words for rain.

701
00:32:24.536 --> 00:32:28.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Right now,
it’s <i>glemmoning </i>out there,

702
00:32:28.295 --> 00:32:29.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and that’s bad.

703
00:32:29.415 --> 00:32:31.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you’re so miserable,

704
00:32:31.334 --> 00:32:32.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
why don’t you take
your <i>Horga’hn</i>

705
00:32:32.654 --> 00:32:34.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and go find some company?

706
00:32:34.293 --> 00:32:37.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you taken a good look
at the Risians lately?

707
00:32:37.253 --> 00:32:39.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They’re even more depressed
than the guests.

708
00:32:41.131 --> 00:32:43.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m trying to organize
a game of hoverball.

709
00:32:43.850 --> 00:32:45.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would either of you
like to join us?

710
00:32:45.290 --> 00:32:46.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In the rain?

711
00:32:46.450 --> 00:32:48.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, on one of the indoor courts.

712
00:32:48.649 --> 00:32:50.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indoor hoverball.

713
00:32:50.289 --> 00:32:52.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s just wrong.

714
00:32:52.528 --> 00:32:53.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll play.

715
00:32:53.767 --> 00:32:56.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good.
That makes one.

716
00:32:56.167 --> 00:32:57.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Having trouble

717
00:32:57.247 --> 00:32:58.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
keeping the guests happy?

718
00:32:58.686 --> 00:33:00.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve never heard
so much complaining in my life.

719
00:33:01.549 --> 00:33:03.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobody came here
to sit around in the rain.

720
00:33:03.165 --> 00:33:04.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not just
the weather.

721
00:33:04.844 --> 00:33:07.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
People are starting
to complain about everything--

722
00:33:07.843 --> 00:33:09.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the rooms, the entertainment,
the food.

723
00:33:09.803 --> 00:33:11.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s wrong with the food?

724
00:33:12.239 --> 00:33:13.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing, as far as I can tell,

725
00:33:13.761 --> 00:33:16.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the guests say
it just doesn’t taste right.

726
00:33:16.480 --> 00:33:17.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s the humidity.

727
00:33:18.406 --> 00:33:19.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It dampens the food,

728
00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:21.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
makes everything mushy.

729
00:33:21.439 --> 00:33:25.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trust me. There’s no word
for "crisp" on Ferenginar.

730
00:33:25.278 --> 00:33:28.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe Mr. Fullerton
was right.

731
00:33:28.237 --> 00:33:31.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we have forgotten
how to deal with adversity.

732
00:33:34.116 --> 00:33:36.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to our figures,
the guest population

733
00:33:36.555 --> 00:33:38.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
has declined by 30 percent
in the last three days.

734
00:33:38.314 --> 00:33:40.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you can be sure
the guests that have stayed

735
00:33:40.314 --> 00:33:42.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
are taking what you
have to say seriously.

736
00:33:42.593 --> 00:33:43.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s a start.

737
00:33:43.833 --> 00:33:45.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One that you can build on.

738
00:33:47.791 --> 00:33:48.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re leaving?

739
00:33:50.950 --> 00:33:53.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have had my fill of Risa.

740
00:33:53.389 --> 00:33:56.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Worf, you’ve been
an inspiration to us all.

741
00:33:56.509 --> 00:33:57.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good luck.

742
00:33:57.989 --> 00:33:58.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

743
00:34:00.667 --> 00:34:03.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You still have the uplink
to the weather control grid?

744
00:34:03.747 --> 00:34:05.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right here.

745
00:34:05.546 --> 00:34:09.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By tomorrow, the weather grid
will be restored to normal,

746
00:34:09.264 --> 00:34:12.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and no one here will remember
this ever happened.

747
00:34:14.943 --> 00:34:17.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I intend to send a message

748
00:34:17.623 --> 00:34:19.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they won’t forget.

749
00:34:29.299 --> 00:34:31.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must be feeling
pretty good right now.

750
00:34:31.378 --> 00:34:34.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The weather’s terrible,
the guests are miserable,

751
00:34:34.257 --> 00:34:36.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and more and more people
are leaving Risa every day.

752
00:34:36.937 --> 00:34:39.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Their response only
proves my point.

753
00:34:39.416 --> 00:34:41.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I see.

754
00:34:41.415 --> 00:34:44.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ruin the vacations
of a few hundred thousand people

755
00:34:45.149 --> 00:34:47.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to bolster the moral fiber
of the Federation.

756
00:34:47.973 --> 00:34:51.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not expect <i>you</i>
to understand.

757
00:34:51.333 --> 00:34:53.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I understand…

758
00:34:53.812 --> 00:34:55.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
even better than you do.

759
00:34:55.771 --> 00:34:58.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What you did had nothing
to do with Risa

760
00:34:58.530 --> 00:35:02.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or the Essentialists,
or even the Federation.

761
00:35:02.969 --> 00:35:05.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s about you and me.

762
00:35:08.767 --> 00:35:11.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You give yourself
far too much credit.

763
00:35:11.126 --> 00:35:12.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do I?

764
00:35:13.885 --> 00:35:17.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think I’m irresponsible,
frivolous…

765
00:35:17.645 --> 00:35:19.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I care more
about pleasure

766
00:35:19.564 --> 00:35:21.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
than I do commitment.

767
00:35:21.963 --> 00:35:25.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you think is going on
between me and Arandis?

768
00:35:25.722 --> 00:35:27.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You <i>know </i>what I think.

769
00:35:29.121 --> 00:35:30.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s right.
I do.

770
00:35:30.681 --> 00:35:32.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you know what?

771
00:35:32.801 --> 00:35:33.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re wrong.

772
00:35:34.800 --> 00:35:35.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did it occur to you

773
00:35:35.799 --> 00:35:37.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to ask me about it?

774
00:35:37.878 --> 00:35:41.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or… trust, just a little?

775
00:35:41.717 --> 00:35:44.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman would not have
given me grounds for suspicion.

776
00:35:44.756 --> 00:35:46.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And how would you know?

777
00:35:46.556 --> 00:35:49.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Curzon spent more time
with Klingons than you ever did.

778
00:35:49.875 --> 00:35:52.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You may have lived
among my people,

779
00:35:53.739 --> 00:35:54.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you are not a Klingon.

780
00:35:54.674 --> 00:35:55.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am.

781
00:35:55.673 --> 00:35:57.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe so,

782
00:35:57.312 --> 00:35:59.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you’re not like
any Klingon I’ve ever met.

783
00:36:01.431 --> 00:36:04.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

784
00:36:04.350 --> 00:36:06.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What happened to you, Worf?

785
00:36:06.509 --> 00:36:10.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re a paragon
of Klingon honor and discipline,

786
00:36:10.228 --> 00:36:12.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but when it comes
to the Klingon

787
00:36:12.348 --> 00:36:14.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
passion for life,
the exuberance,

788
00:36:14.587 --> 00:36:16.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the enjoyment of the moment,

789
00:36:16.707 --> 00:36:19.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you are constantly
holding yourself back.

790
00:36:19.866 --> 00:36:21.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

791
00:36:21.585 --> 00:36:23.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is not the issue here.

792
00:36:23.944 --> 00:36:24.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think it is.

793
00:36:28.623 --> 00:36:31.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not wish
to lose you, Jadzia.

794
00:36:32.223 --> 00:36:34.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then talk to me, <i>please.</i>

795
00:36:40.460 --> 00:36:41.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know from the age of seven,

796
00:36:42.595 --> 00:36:44.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was raised by humans
on the farm world of Gault.

797
00:36:44.618 --> 00:36:47.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was a sparsely
populated world,

798
00:36:47.138 --> 00:36:48.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no more than 20,000 inhabitants.

799
00:36:50.696 --> 00:36:54.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It often seemed as though
everyone knew everybody else,

800
00:36:54.957 --> 00:36:55.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but one thing <i>was </i>for certain.

801
00:36:55.375 --> 00:36:56.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everybody knew me.

802
00:36:56.735 --> 00:37:00.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was the Klingon child,
the uncontrollable one.

803
00:37:00.494 --> 00:37:02.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was the biggest,
the strongest,

804
00:37:02.333 --> 00:37:04.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the most fearless child
on the entire planet.

805
00:37:04.812 --> 00:37:07.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I fought hard, played hard,
did as I pleased.

806
00:37:07.851 --> 00:37:10.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What changed?

807
00:37:10.570 --> 00:37:15.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I was 13, I was captain
of my school soccer team.

808
00:37:15.329 --> 00:37:19.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had made the championships,
and I was determined to win.

809
00:37:20.799 --> 00:37:21.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Near the end of the second half
with the score tied,

810
00:37:22.472 --> 00:37:24.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
my team got
a corner kick.

811
00:37:24.686 --> 00:37:26.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ball
sailed up high.

812
00:37:26.845 --> 00:37:29.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Both I and one of my opponents,
a human boy named Mikel,

813
00:37:29.925 --> 00:37:32.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
leapt up to head the ball.

814
00:37:32.884 --> 00:37:38.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He had position,
but I was determined to score.

815
00:37:38.824 --> 00:37:40.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I remember laughing
with excitement

816
00:37:40.762 --> 00:37:42.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as I threw myself at him.

817
00:37:45.803 --> 00:37:46.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go on.

818
00:37:48.359 --> 00:37:49.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighing </i>)

819
00:37:49.759 --> 00:37:50.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The next thing I knew,

820
00:37:50.998 --> 00:37:52.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the ball was sailing
into their goal.

821
00:37:53.380 --> 00:37:56.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I roared with triumph

822
00:37:56.517 --> 00:37:58.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and turned around to Mikel
to gloat,

823
00:37:58.756 --> 00:38:01.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
only to find him lying
in the grass bleeding.

824
00:38:01.715 --> 00:38:03.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our heads
had collided

825
00:38:04.751 --> 00:38:05.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when we both went up
for the ball.

826
00:38:05.914 --> 00:38:07.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I had not felt the impact,

827
00:38:07.954 --> 00:38:11.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I had broken his neck,
and…

828
00:38:11.152 --> 00:38:12.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he died the next day.

829
00:38:15.951 --> 00:38:17.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was an accident.

830
00:38:17.631 --> 00:38:19.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which only makes it worse.

831
00:38:19.510 --> 00:38:23.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Compared to Klingons,
humans are fragile creatures.

832
00:38:23.709 --> 00:38:25.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I realized at that moment

833
00:38:25.868 --> 00:38:29.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to live among them,
I must practice restraint.

834
00:38:29.707 --> 00:38:32.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That must have been
difficult for you.

835
00:38:32.266 --> 00:38:33.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At first.

836
00:38:34.256 --> 00:38:36.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In time, it became a part
of who I was--

837
00:38:36.705 --> 00:38:39.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who… I am.

838
00:38:40.944 --> 00:38:43.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you’re still afraid
that if you lose control…

839
00:38:47.302 --> 00:38:50.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Someone I care about
might get hurt.

840
00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:55.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That explains a lot…

841
00:38:57.178 --> 00:38:59.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you have to realize

842
00:38:59.258 --> 00:39:01.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there are some things
in life you can’t control,

843
00:39:01.857 --> 00:39:04.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and one of them is me.

844
00:39:04.577 --> 00:39:07.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But what you can do is trust me.

845
00:39:07.176 --> 00:39:10.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I care about
you, Worf,

846
00:39:10.335 --> 00:39:13.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I would never do
anything to hurt you.

847
00:39:13.854 --> 00:39:16.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nor would I do
anything to hurt you.

848
00:39:19.132 --> 00:39:21.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who knows?

849
00:39:21.211 --> 00:39:24.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I may have more self-control
than you give me credit for.

850
00:39:25.969 --> 00:39:27.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>objects clattering </i>)

851
00:39:27.730 --> 00:39:29.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That felt like
an earthquake.

852
00:39:29.929 --> 00:39:32.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>rumbling </i>)

853
00:39:32.248 --> 00:39:33.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So did that.

854
00:39:33.687 --> 00:39:35.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Essentialists.

855
00:39:37.287 --> 00:39:38.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should see them all run.

856
00:39:39.464 --> 00:39:41.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think they finally realized
that the party’s over.

857
00:39:41.566 --> 00:39:42.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Increase the feedback

858
00:39:42.805 --> 00:39:44.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the tectonic
stress regulators.

859
00:39:44.846 --> 00:39:45.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I do, there won’t be

860
00:39:45.404 --> 00:39:47.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a building left standing
on this part of Risa.

861
00:39:48.803 --> 00:39:50.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It might be
a good idea

862
00:39:50.122 --> 00:39:51.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to head to
the spaceport.

863
00:39:53.121 --> 00:39:55.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or at least get
out of this room.

864
00:39:57.321 --> 00:39:58.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very well.

865
00:39:58.640 --> 00:40:01.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think our work
is done here.

866
00:40:01.239 --> 00:40:02.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WORF:
The uplink--

867
00:40:02.759 --> 00:40:03.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
give it to me.

868
00:40:04.392 --> 00:40:05.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, I suggest

869
00:40:05.638 --> 00:40:07.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you all get off this planet
as soon as possible.

870
00:40:07.918 --> 00:40:09.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have no wish to see you

871
00:40:09.677 --> 00:40:10.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or your
friends harmed.

872
00:40:10.637 --> 00:40:11.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Give us the uplink,

873
00:40:11.916 --> 00:40:13.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or the only person
who will be harmed is you.

874
00:40:18.234 --> 00:40:19.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you were
one of us.

875
00:40:20.743 --> 00:40:23.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps I was for a
time, but I believe

876
00:40:23.313 --> 00:40:25.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Federation will survive
the Dominion, the Borg,

877
00:40:25.512 --> 00:40:27.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and people like you.

878
00:40:27.271 --> 00:40:28.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf…

879
00:40:28.431 --> 00:40:29.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if you walk out of here now,

880
00:40:30.310 --> 00:40:31.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’ll be turning your back
on the Federation.

881
00:40:31.550 --> 00:40:32.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t you see?

882
00:40:32.830 --> 00:40:34.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Overindulgence,
lack of self-control--

883
00:40:34.750 --> 00:40:37.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they’ll destroy
everything we hold dear,

884
00:40:37.509 --> 00:40:39.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you will be responsible.

885
00:40:39.268 --> 00:40:40.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say that we have to return

886
00:40:40.707 --> 00:40:42.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to traditional
Federation values.

887
00:40:42.147 --> 00:40:43.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I agree,

888
00:40:43.227 --> 00:40:47.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but one of those
values is trust.

889
00:40:47.106 --> 00:40:51.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is essential that
we remember that.

890
00:40:51.704 --> 00:40:53.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t you walk away from <i>me.</i>

891
00:40:58.102 --> 00:41:00.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will do as I please.

892
00:41:02.101 --> 00:41:03.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>groaning </i>)

893
00:41:07.420 --> 00:41:09.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am on vacation.

894
00:41:17.697 --> 00:41:20.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Figures-- the weather
improves the day we leave.

895
00:41:20.936 --> 00:41:23.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t wait
to get home.

896
00:41:23.455 --> 00:41:26.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not that I didn’t
enjoy myself.

897
00:41:26.334 --> 00:41:28.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d better
go find Bashir.

898
00:41:28.573 --> 00:41:30.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He brought a <i>Horga’hn</i>
down to breakfast,

899
00:41:30.373 --> 00:41:31.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that’s the last
I saw of him.

900
00:41:33.732 --> 00:41:35.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope the two of you
enjoyed Risa

901
00:41:36.517 --> 00:41:37.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and will come again.

902
00:41:37.450 --> 00:41:40.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not think that
I would be welcome.

903
00:41:40.130 --> 00:41:41.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you still have

904
00:41:41.169 --> 00:41:42.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a lot to learn
about our people.

905
00:41:42.849 --> 00:41:46.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never got a chance
to say good-bye to Curzon Dax.

906
00:41:46.728 --> 00:41:48.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you’re not saying
good-bye to me either.

907
00:41:48.688 --> 00:41:49.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll be back.

908
00:41:52.286 --> 00:41:54.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And Risa will be waiting.

909
00:41:57.685 --> 00:41:59.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what do we do now?

910
00:41:59.964 --> 00:42:03.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now we watch
the suns set.

911
00:42:03.242 --> 00:42:05.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a better idea.

912
00:42:05.442 --> 00:42:07.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t we go swimming?

